The Board of Directors of Nigerian Breweries Plc has appointed Mrs.Yeliz Yedikardesler as a Non-Executive Director with effect from April 1, 2022. Yedikardesler, who is the Senior Director, Finance; Africa, Middle East, and Eastern Europe of Heineken, is expected to bring her wealth of experience and knowledge on the Board and the company. Before joining the Heineken Group in March 2022, she was the Regional Finance Director, Mars Wrigley Middle East Africa (MEA), Mars Incorporated, Dubai, United Arab (UAE), where she spent 17 years and held senior roles. Her work experience spans over 23 years in the fast-moving consumer goods (FMCG) industry with specialisation in commercial and financial management, financial operations, strategy development, risk management, corporate finance, sustainability and governance, transformational projects and business integration.   ‘Access Bank, supporter of women-led businesses’     Daily Need Group opens clinic     Lagos urges private sector to drive innovations in…   In a related development, the Board accepted the resignation of Steven Siemer as Non-Executive Director effective March 31, 2022. Siemer joined the Board in 2018 and made excellent contributions to the company’s growth. Incorporated in 1946, Nigerian Breweries is the country’s pioneer and largest brewer firm with nine breweries, two malting plants, and 26 sales depots.     With a market capitalisation of N448 billion, it is one of the largest companies on the Nigerian Exchange Limited.